\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F. Set a rack on a rimmed baking sheet.\
Lay the pancetta slices on the rack on the baking sheet and bake until {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/crisp/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 crisp}}, 15 to 18 minutes.\
Meanwhile, set your toaster to a low setting and toast the brioche slices, (they should be slightly dry but not brown).\
Lay 4 slices lightly toasted {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/brioche/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 brioche}} on a work surface and cover the slices with half the cheese, followed by a slice of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/tomato/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 tomato}}. Season each sandwich with a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pinch/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 pinch}} of salt and a healthy grind of black pepper. Top each with 2 pancetta rounds and the remaining {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cheese/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cheese}}. Lay the remaining brioche slices on top and press down lightly. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/butter/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Butter}} the top of each sandwich with 1/2 tablespoon butter.\
Heat a large griddle pan over medium heat.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/melt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Melt}} the remaining tablespoon butter on the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/griddle/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 griddle}} pan and add the sandwiches, buttered side up. Cook until the bread is golden brown and the cheese is beginning to melt. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/flip/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Flip}} the sandwiches, press lightly, and continue cooking until golden and toasty. Transfer to a cutting board and slice the sandwiches with a serrated knife, on the diagonal. Arrange on a serving platter and serve immediately.}